We live in a safe area in the centre of London, and all areas in the city are easily accessible from here.
Our apartment is comfortable and bright with high ceilings. Its ideal for the single traveler who wants warmth, safety, comfort, and practicality.

The space
The bedroom is a good size double. Its practical and very comfortable.

The familys bedrooms (3) are on a different floor.

Guest access
Bedroom, corridors, toilet, bathroom and kitchen

During your stay
We are always happy to socialise with guests. However, we are equally happy to give them privacy, and let them have a quiet time while staying at our place.

Other things to note
The guest bedroom is on the ground-floor, and the toilet and shared bathroom are on the first floor.

We live in front of a relatively busy road, so expect to hear, during the day, a bit of traffic noise.

Where youll be

Greater London, England, United Kingdom
This listing's location is verified and the exact location will be provided after booking.

Neighborhood highlights

The neighbourhood is relatively quiet, with only some noise caused by traffic and passersby, and hardly any from neighbours.
There are plenty of restaurants (I like Goya, on Lupus St) and shops nearby, as well as Tate Britain Gallery.
The apartment is on walking distance of Victoria, Westminster, Saint Jamess Park and Buckingham Palace.
